description:
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a team at an exciting stage as it takes responsibility for developing and delivering secure software solutions using modern frameworks and practices initially on a greenfield solution. Working in an Agile environment you should be able to work within a cross-functional team being proactive to drive continuous improvement in our software, techniques and processes. You will bring expertise to help innovate and drive our team forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technical skills required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years experience with any modern JavaScript framework, preference is Angular&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good CSS/style organisation (knowledge of Less or Sass pre-processors)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grunt, Gulp, Webpack or similar task/build runner tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsive design, mobile first&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consuming REST services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Writing Front End tests (protractor, karma, Jasmine or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid grounding in current UI design patterns, practices and frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of teaching/mentoring/pair-programming with other members of the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advantageous:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of Docker&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using a TDD approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in a Continuous Delivery or Deployment environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of using Azure/AWS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Richard Leonard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head of Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: richard.leonard@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
